function getThreeCharCodeFromFilename(filename) {
  const regex = /\b(\d+[A-Za-z]+)\.\w+\b/; // Regex to match three chars code with digits or letters before .usfm
  const matches = filename.match(regex);

  if (matches && matches.length === 2) {
    return matches[1]; // Return the matched group which is our desired Code
  } else {
    throw new Error('No match found for three character code in provided filename');
  }
}

// Example usage:
const file = "57-1Jn.usfm";
try {
  const code = getThreeCharCodeFromFilename(file);
  console.log(`The extracted code is ${code}`); // Outputs '1Jn' as the three character code from filename
} catch (error) {
  console.error(error.message);
}
```
This JavaScript function uses a regular expression to match and extract exactly three characters composed of digits or letters before ".usfm" in any given string that represents a file name, ensuring it meets the described criteria. It also includes error handling for when no valid code is found within the filename provided.
